Carrefour Makes New Pay Offer to Workers, La Tribune Says

-- B y   A n d r e w   R o b e r t s
-- 
2011-04-14T05:45:02Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-14/carrefour-makes-new-pay-offer-to-workers-la-tribune-says.html
Carrefour SA (CA)  offered to increase
pay in its superstores by 2 percent following an April 9 strike,
La Tribune  reported , citing unions.  Carrefour also proposed a one-time bonus of 220 euros
($319) and to raise to 10 percent from 7 percent a staff
discount, the French newspaper said. Carrefour has offered to
pay workers for the hours lost to the strike, which took place
in 150 of its stores, La Tribune said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
 Andrew Roberts  in Paris at 
 aroberts36@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Celeste Perri at   cperri@bloomberg.net . 